Powered by RubiQube Ad Network The Economic and Financial Crimes Commission, EFCC, Lagos Zonal Office, have arrested one Frank Chinedu,22, the proprietor of a Yahoo Yahoo training school, in Lagos. Tony Orilade, Acting Head, Media and Publicity, EFCC told the Daily Independent that the proprietor,was arrested alongside eight students of the unnamed training centre located at 14, Animashaun Street, Progressive Estate, Ojodu Berger, Lagos, while receiving lectures on internet fraud activities. He gave names of the suspects as Ahmed Musa, 24; Desmond Eze, 29; Preye Kingsley, 23; Benjamin Irabor, 21; Benjamin Opah, 19; Akapo Prosper, 22; Innocent Paul, 20 and Olamide Edun, 20. Orilade said the suspected internet fraudsters were arrested by the EFCC undercover operatives on May 22, 2019, following intelligence reports received by the Commission about their involvement in alleged criminal activities. Items recovered from the suspects at the point of arrest include nine laptops, 16 mobile phones, an Airtel modem, Orange Wifi and one Toyota Camry with registration number EPE406FN. He said the suspects will soon be charged to court.